Ignoring the threat to swap my crucial bishop.  If I take on h6, his Q is invited into the heart of my defence and is difficult to shift.  If White takes on g7, the K prevents the Q from approaching without further preparation.  I launch a counter-attack, gaining space on the Q-side.  If I withstand the attack on the kingside, this will give me a long term advantage.
